# hub/.gcloudignore (mission-50 T3 — closes bug-36)
#
# `gcloud builds submit` reads `.gcloudignore` if present, else falls back to
# `.gitignore`. `hub/.gitignore` excludes `ois-storage-provider-*.tgz`
# (intentional, to prevent accidental commits of the transient tarball staged
# by `scripts/local/build-hub.sh`). Without this `.gcloudignore`, that
# exclusion propagates to the Cloud Build upload context and Step
# `COPY ois-storage-provider-*.tgz` fails because the tarball is missing.
#
# This file is self-contained (does NOT use `#!include:.gitignore`). We mirror
# the meaningful excludes here, then re-include the staged tarball.
#
# TODO(idea-186): when npm workspaces lands, this file + the hub/.gitignore
# tarball exclusion + the build-hub.sh transient-swap mechanic + the
# Dockerfile COPY lines all become obsolete. Sunset together — see
# `deploy/README.md` §"Cloud Build tarball staging (mission-50)" for the full
# cleanup list.

node_modules/

# Re-include the storage-provider tarball staged by scripts/local/build-hub.sh.
# (The leading `!` is documentation-style here — with self-contained
# .gcloudignore there's no prior exclusion to override — but it makes intent
# explicit and stays correct if a broader exclude is added above.)
!ois-storage-provider-*.tgz
